      "line": 70,
      "message": "This is the original server name against which this query is written and which is included in the sample custom query response. I have also included \"OzVserver\" and \"testVserverName\" to match against this query response because those are used in many of the use cases. What this code essentially does is: It will return a valid response if the vserver name is any of these three values. If it it is anything else, it will return a null. I had to do this to make sure all the control loop test cases work correctly.",
